INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to for-hire vehicle licenses.
EventItemMatterName: For-hire vehicle licenses.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring motion detectors for commercial buildings.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring motion detectors for commercial buildings.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to publishing open data.
EventItemMatterName: Publishing open data.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to prohibiting general vendors from leaving pushcarts, stands or goods unattended.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting general vendors from leaving pushcarts, stands or goods unattended.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to extending J-51 benefits to owners of multiple dwellings for green roofs.
EventItemMatterName: Extending J-51 benefits to owners of multiple dwellings for green roofs.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Small Business
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to introduce, and the Governor to sign, legislation which would authorize municipalities to create a loan program to assist small business owners in securing commercial lease space.
EventItemMatterName: Authorize municipalities to create a loan program to assist small business owners in securing commercial lease space.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to notifying tenants of city-owned buildings about the potential for tenant ownership prior to disposition.
EventItemMatterName: Notifying tenants of city-owned buildings about the potential for tenant ownership prior to disposition.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Re-referred to Committee by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the United States Congress to pass the Breast Cancer Patient Protection Act of 2009 (S. 688/H.R. 1691).
EventItemMatterName: Congress to pass the Breast Cancer Patient Protection Act of 2005 (S. 688/H.R. 1691).

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education to develop a plan for the construction and/or renovation of school gymnasiums as part of its Five-Year Capital Plan to ensure that every school has adequate facilities in order to comply with New York State physical education requirements and to provide for healthy children and youth.
EventItemMatterName: Dept of Education to develop a plan for the construction and/or renovation of school gymnasiums as part of its Five-Year Capital Plan.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the regulation of horse drawn cabs and repealing section 17-333 of the administrative code.
EventItemMatterName: Regulation of horse drawn cabs.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to vending in Sunset Park, Brooklyn.
EventItemMatterName: Vending in Sunset Park, Brooklyn.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Juvenile Justice
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of juvenile justice to report on demographic data.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the department of juvenile justice to report on demographic data.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to banning the release of certain birds for ceremonial purposes.
EventItemMatterName: Banning the release of certain birds for ceremonial purposes.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Youth Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to pitching by high school children in competitive baseball games.
EventItemMatterName: Pitching by high school children in competitive baseball games.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring exterior lighting to contain fully shielded fixtures.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring exterior lighting to contain fully shielded fixtures.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the re-keying of lock cylinders in the entrance doors of multiple dwelling units at the beginning of each new tenancy.
EventItemMatterName: The re-keying of lock cylinders in the entrance doors of multiple dwelling units at the beginning of each new tenancy.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to an owner’s duty to purchase and install radiator covers.
EventItemMatterName: An owner’s duty to purchase and install radiator covers.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to prohibiting obstructions or nuisances in or upon sidewalks, flagging or curbstones, streets and medians of streets and establishing a rebuttable presumption regarding responsibility for the placement of signs constituting such obstructions or nuisances.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting obstructing signs on sidewalks, flagging and curbstone whether or not abutting the offending property.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to creating one day temporary parking permits.
EventItemMatterName: Creating one day temporary parking permits.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to allowing wheelchair accessible taxicabs to use Express Lanes or High Occupancy Vehicle (HOV) lanes.
EventItemMatterName: Allowing wheelchair accessible taxicabs to use Express Lanes or High Occupancy Vehicle (HOV) lanes.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the creation of an office of road safety within the department of transportation.
EventItemMatterName: Creation of an office of road safety within the department of transportation.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of transportation to create a plan for parking motorcycles.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the department of transportation to create a plan for parking motorcycles.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to an annual census of vacant properties.
EventItemMatterName: Annual census of vacant properties.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to prohibiting the display of wild or exotic animals for public entertainment or amusement.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting the display of wild or exotic animals for public entertainment or amusement.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the United States Congress to reintroduce and pass legislation that would amend the Public Health Service Act with respect to facilitating the development of microbicides for preventing transmission of HIV and other diseases.
EventItemMatterName: Public Health Service Act with respect to facilitating the development of microbicides for preventing transmission of HIV and other diseases.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Waterfronts
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to the waterfront management advisory board.
EventItemMatterName: Waterfront management advisory board.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Waterfronts
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to creating a clean waterfront plan.
EventItemMatterName: Creating a clean waterfront plan.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Waterfronts
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to increasing fines for violations of the law for illegal dumping along waterfront property into New York city waterways.
EventItemMatterName: Increasing fines for violations of the law for illegal dumping along Waterfront property into NYC waterways.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to testing of local fish for health related risks and posting of subsistence fishing warnings in appropriate locations and conducting a public education campaign.
EventItemMatterName: Testing of local fish for health related risks and posting of subsistence fishing warnings in appropriate locations and conducting a public education campaign.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the State Legislature and the Governor to support the passage of  A.5745 and S.3645 which would reinstate the modest tax on non-City residents known as the “commuter tax”  in the wake of the economic crisis facing New York City, so that New York City can continue to provide an adequate level of services to those who work and live in the City and can continue to serve as the economic engine for the state.
EventItemMatterName: Reinstate the modest tax on non-City residents known as the “commuter tax” in the wake of the economic crisis facing NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to cellular telephone service equipment and the inspection of the exterior walls of buildings greater than six stories in height.
EventItemMatterName: Cellular telephone service equipment and the inspection of the exterior walls of buildings greater than six stories in height.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to biological, chemical and radiological detectors.
EventItemMatterName: Biological, chemical and radiological detectors.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to amend the state’s Criminal Procedure Law to authorize a judge to consider a defendant’s “danger to the community” as a factor in bail decisions.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the state’s Criminal Procedure Law to authorize a judge to consider a defendant’s “danger to the community” as a factor in bail decisions.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education to eliminate the fingerprinting fee for individuals seeking to volunteer in New York City public schools.
EventItemMatterName: Dept of Education to eliminate the fingerprinting fee for individuals seeking to volunteer in NYC public schools.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the department of education to distribute information on obtaining a library card and a library card application to all students.
